    <body>
      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="875-29DI">
          <head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-875-29DI-headnote-1">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-875-29DI-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-875-29DI-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">The following Poem was sent from <hi rend="italics">Dublin</hi>──The Subject of it is, a certain <hi rend="italics">Dean</hi>, a very popular Person in that Country. For the explaining the Occasion of it, we need only advise the Readers, that the said <hi rend="italics">Dean</hi> has purchased a Piece of Ground from a certain Gentleman there, call'd Sir <hi rend="italics">Arthur</hi>, and is building a House, which he calls <hi rend="italics">Drapier's Hall</hi>, at the Request of the said Sir <hi rend="italics">Arthur</hi>.</l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-875-29DI-headnote-2">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-875-29DI-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-875-29DI-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-875-29DI-headnote-3">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-875-29DI-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-875-29DI-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29DI-line-1" n="1"><hi rend="display-initial">W</hi>E give the World to understand,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29DI-line-2" n="2">Our thriving <hi rend="italics">Dean</hi> has purchased Land,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29DI-line-3" n="3">A Purchase which will bring him clear,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29DI-line-4" n="4">Above his Rent, four Pound a Year;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29DI-line-5" n="5">Provided to improve the Ground,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29DI-line-6" n="6">He will but add two hundred Pound;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29DI-line-7" n="7">And from his endless hoarded Store,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29DI-line-8" n="8">To build a House five hundred more.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29DI-line-9" n="9">Sir <hi rend="italics">Arthur</hi> too, shall have his Will,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29DI-line-10" n="10">And call the Mansion <hi rend="italics">Drapier'</hi>s<hi rend="italics"> Hill</hi>,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29DI-line-11" n="11">That when a Nation long en────d,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29DI-line-12" n="12">Forgets by whom it once was saved;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29DI-line-13" n="13">When none the <hi rend="italics">Drapier</hi>'s Praise shall sing,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29DI-line-14" n="14">His <hi rend="italics">Signs</hi> aloft no longer swing,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29DI-line-15" n="15">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29DI-line-16" n="16">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29DI-line-17" n="17">His <hi rend="italics">Medals</hi> and his <hi rend="italics">Prints</hi> forgotten,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29DI-line-18" n="18">And all his Handkerchiefs are rotten;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29DI-line-19" n="19">His <hi rend="italics">famous Letters</hi> made waste Paper,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29DI-line-20" n="20">This <hi rend="italics">Hill</hi> may keep the Name of <hi rend="italics">Drapier</hi>,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29DI-line-21" n="21">In spight of Envy flourish still,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-29DI-line-22" n="22">And <hi rend="italics">Drapiers</hi> vye with <hi rend="italics">Cooper'</hi>s<hi rend="italics"> Hill</hi>.</l>
          </lg>
